<title>CSS Writing Modes reference</title>

<style>
div {
  writing-mode: vertical-rl;
  font: 32px serif;
  margin: 1em;
  padding: .25em;
  border: 1px solid gray;
}
span {
  text-combine-upright: all;
}
#ref span {
  unicode-bidi: bidi-override;
  direction: ltr;
}
</style>

Both boxes should render the same:

<div id=ref>
<p>foo<span>א</span>bar</p>
<p>foo<span>בא</span>bar</p>
<p>foo<span>גבא</span>bar</p>
<p>foo<span>דגבא</span>bar</p>
</div>

<div id=ref>
<p>foo<span>א</span>bar</p>
<p>foo<span>בא</span>bar</p>
<p>foo<span>גבא</span>bar</p>
<p>foo<p>foo<p>foo<p>foo<p>foo<p>foo<p>foo<p>foo<span>דגבא</span>bar</p>bar</p>bar</p>bar</p>bar</p>bar</p>bar</p>bar</p>
</div>
